\section{Conclusion}
\frame{
  \frametitle{Conclusion}
  \begin{itemize}
    \item Advantage: Its flexible, efficient and deals with
      non-stationarity.
    \item Also enabling to observe patterns that were difficult to
      observe in the original plot.
    \item limitation: need to obtain a sensible set of frequency. Can
      be difficult when the series contain too much noises.
    \item Statistics can be produced from the decomposition for market
      segmentation through cluster analysis.
   \end{itemize}
}

